The House of Representatives yesterday, vowed to disappoint critics who allegedly labelled it a “rubber stamp National Assembly for approving and passing the 2020 budget estimates.” Chairman of the House Committee on Media and Public Affairs, Hon. Benjamin  Kalu made the vow yesterday  while addressing journalists at the National Assembly complex. Kalu said that the 9th Assembly would disappoint the people who call it a “rubber stamp” assembly as a result of the speedy passage of the 2020 budget and the Finance Bill sent by President Muhammadu Buhari to the lawmakers. He noted that the House has set out goals to be achieved, and is aimed at bringing needed development and transformations to the lives of Nigerians. It would be recalled that a section of Nigerians had raised questions over the speedy passage of the 2020 budget as well as the N3.7 billion approved by President for the renovation of the National Assembly complex.